      "id": 359543,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Benzyl chloride can be converted into benzaldehyde by treatment with nitromethane and base. The reaction involves initial conversion of nitromethane into its anion, followed by S<sub>N</sub>2 reaction of the anion with benzyl chloride and subsequent E2 reaction. Write the mechanism in detail, using curved arrows to indicate the electron flow in each step.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdmdWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--9a3b39625897e5fb1f03c5a8a66906e4d4145a10/OChem_17_EC_043.jpg\" alt=\"Benzyl chloride reacts with nitromethane anion to form benzaldehyde.\">",
